{"title_page": "Rebecca Vincent", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rebecca Vincent\n| birth_date         = {{Birth year and age|1983}}<ref name=\"Turin1\">{{cite news | title = Rebecca Vincent: ?Speak out against human rights abuses? | newspaper = Turan Information Agency | location = Azerbaijan | date = November 13, 2013}}</ref>\n| nationality        = American<br>British\n}}\n\n'''Rebecca Vincent''' is an American journalist, human rights activist, and former human rights officer at the US embassy in [[Azerbaijan]].<ref name=\"Turin1\"/> \n\nIn 2012 the [[Azerbaijani government|Azerbaijani Government]] banned Vincent from the country after she attended an art exhibition there called ''\"Sing for Democracy.\"''  The government described her attendance as \"interference in the internal affairs of the country\".<ref>{{cite news | title = ART FOR DEMOCRACY campaign announces a new contest | newspaper = Turan Information Agency | location = Azerbaijan | date = August 16, 2013}}</ref> \n\nVincent served as the coordinator for the Sport for Rights campaign while working with [[Article 19]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Azeri news agency accuses USA of \"smear campaign\" plan ahead of European Games | newspaper = BBC Monitoring Trans Caucasus Unit | date = April 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Amnesty International, 'Article 19' competing to defame Azerbaijan | newspaper = Trend Daily News | location = Azerbaijan | date = June 18, 2015}}</ref> She is currently director of the London bureau of [[Reporters Without Borders]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://rsf.org/en/news/rsf-appoints-rebecca-vincent-director-its-new-london-bureau | title = RSF Appoints Rebecca Vincent Director of its New London Bureau | date = September 27, 2016 | website = Reporters Without Borders | access-date = May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vincent, Rebecca}}\n[[Category:American women journalists]]\n[[Category:Human rights activists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n\n\n{{US-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rebecca Vincent\n| birth_date         = {{Birth year and age|1983}}<ref name=\"Turin1\">{{cite news | title = Rebecca Vincent: ?Speak out against human rights abuses? | newspaper = Turan Information Agency | location = Azerbaijan | date = November 13, 2013}}</ref>\n| nationality        = American<br>British\n}}\n\n'''Rebecca Vincent''' is an American journalist, human rights activist, and former human rights officer at the US embassy in [[Azerbaijan]].<ref name=\"Turin1\"/> \n\nIn 2012 the [[Azerbaijani government|Azerbaijani Government]] banned Vincent from the country after she attended an art exhibition there called''\"Sing for Democracy.''  The government described her attendence as \"interference in the internal affairs of the country\".<ref>{{cite news | title = ART FOR DEMOCRACY campaign announces a new contest | newspaper = Turan Information Agency | location = Azerbaijan | date = August 16, 2013}}</ref> \n\nVincent served as the coordinator for the Sport for Rights campaign while working with [[Article 19]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Azeri news agency accuses USA of \"smear campaign\" plan ahead of European Games | newspaper = BBC Monitoring Trans Caucasus Unit | date = April 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Amnesty International, 'Article 19' competing to defame Azerbaijan | newspaper = Trend Daily News | location = Azerbaijan | date = June 18, 2015}}</ref> She is currently director of the London bureau of [[Reporters Without Borders]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://rsf.org/en/news/rsf-appoints-rebecca-vincent-director-its-new-london-bureau | title = RSF Appoints Rebecca Vincent Director of its New London Bureau | date = September 27, 2016 | website = Reporters Without Borders | access-date = May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSOR